annotationA: Oculocerebrorenal syndrome of Lowe (Ocrl) is an inositol polyphosphate 5-phosphatase that regulates PtdIns(4,5)P2 homeostasis by dephosphorylating PtdIns(4,5)P2 on endocytic compartments. In vitro experiments also suggest a role of Ocrl during cytokinesis
annotationB: Sorting nexin 6, isoform B; Protein transporter activity; phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: retrograde transport, endosome to Golgi; intracellular protein transport
